713695f-a.text:
106-108 East 54th Street, adjoining and east of the S.E. corner
of Park Ave.
About 1912.

722261f.text:
401 Park Avenue, at N.E. corner of 54th Street, showing a newly
completed prize-winning apartment house, 12 stories tall.
On the farther side of the garage, which will stay, another apartement
house will be erected in 1916.
Note the temporary wooden fence. The railroad tracks have been electrified
and covered over, but the center perks have not yet been constructed.
1913.

Wurts Bros., Photographers.
Gift of E.M. Jenks.
Neg. #1734

722266f-a.text:
Park Avenue, West side, between 54th and 53rd Streets, the oldest complete block in this part of the Avenue, dating back to the
1890's or earlier.
These houses may be identified on 1905 photographs which show
Open railroad yards where the street now runs.
April 1928.
P.L. Sperr, photographer.
